window.__KB.push({"t": "Personal Assistant (PA) Registration Application Form Important Note: 1. Please ", "f": "AS03.pdf", "s": "Personal Assistant (PA) Registration Application Form Important Note: 1. Please submit : (i) duly completed and signed PA Registration Application Form and the attached 2 copies of “Non-Disclosure Agreement”, (ii) a photocopy of the PA’s Hong Kong Identity Card (HKID) and (iii) 2 recent color passport-sized photos (L: 2.9 cm, W: 2.5 cm) to Agency Support at MT22. 2. □ Please tick the appropriate box. 3. # Please delete as appropriate. Part A: Type of PA Registration Application □ New Registration Application for Personal Assistant. □ New Registration Application for District Secretary, only 1 District Secretary is allowed for each District □ Application for Changing/Removing Hiring Agent(s): Existing PA Code: ______________________ Photo 1 L: 2.9 cm W: 2.5 cm Photo 2 L: 2.9 cm W: 2.5 cm Part B: PA Information Name in English: Name in Chinese: HKID Card No.: Gender#: (same as HKID Card) (same as HKID Card) Other Name: MT / MFC / MP / LMC ( Office Location#: GW Tower ( ),Suite ( () Contact No.: Male / Female )/F ) (Mobile) Part C: Hiring Agent(s) Information (Maximum 4 Hiring Agents) NamePrimary*: Mobile: Agent Code: Name2nd: Mobile: Agent Code: Name3rd: Mobile: Agent Code: Name4th: Mobile: Agent Code: District Code: District Code: District Code: District Code: * Each primary hiring agent will be granted one PA Manutouch account for their PA. Regardless of the number of PAs an agent hired, only one PA will be granted access to the PA Manutouch account. Additionally, the PA will only have access rights to the PA Manutouch account associated with their primary hiring agent. Therefore, even if a PA is hired by multiple agents, they can only access the PA Manutouch account of their primary hiring agent. Terms and Conditions: 1. The PA Card and Access Card should not be borrowed / used by anyone other than the PA or the agent(s) who employ(s) or appoint(s) the PA (the “Hiring Agent(s)”) 2. This Application should be countersigned by District Director or above. 3. If the PA is employed or appointed by more than one Hiring Agent (maximum 4 Hiring Agents) at the same time, unless provided otherwise, the liabilities of the Hiring Agents to Manulife (International) Limited (“Manulife”) under these Terms and Conditions shall be joint and several. 4. One agent can hire maximum 4 PAs. 5. Only one PA is allowed as District Secretary in a District. 6. The PA must carry his/her PA Card and Access Card at all times within the office premises of Manulife for identification purpose. 7. A handling fee of HK$200 shall be charged to the Primary Hiring Agent for re-issuing a replacement PA Card and a handling fee of HK$100 shall be charged to the Primary Hiring Agent for re-issuing a replacement Access Card. For termination of the employment or appointment of the PA or resignation of the PA, the Primary Hiring Agent shall notify Manulife by submitting PA Deregistration Form no less than 7 working days before the PA’s last working day. The Primary Hiring Agent shall return the PA Card and Access Card to Manulife on or before the PA’s last working day. Failure to return or delay in returning the PA Card and Access Card shall lead to a HK$200 penalty fee for the PA Card and a HK$100 penalty fee for the Access Card payable by the Primary Hiring Agent immediately. 8. Both the PA and the Hiring Agent(s) shall be liable for all improper usages of the PA Card, Access Card and if applicable the PA Manutouch Account granted by Manulife. The PA and the Hiring Agent(s) shall indemnify Manulife for all demands, claims, loss, damages and expenses arising out of any improper and/or illegal use of the PA Card, Access Card and PA Manutouch Account. The liability of the PA and the Hiring Agent(s) is joint and several. 9. The provision of the information required in this form is a condition for the issuance of the PA Card and Access Card. The Hiring agent(s) must ensure that they have complied with all the necessary requirements under the Personal Data (Privacy) Ordinance in obtaining and/or transferring the PA’s personal data to Manulife. The PA and the Hiring Agent(s) hereby declare that they have verified the correctness of the PA’s personal data. 10. PA Training Guide: 10.1 The Primary Hiring Agent must download the PA Training Guide from Manutouch (Resources > Document library > Agency Support > Personal Assistant > PA Training Guide (Compliance Section)) and provide a copy of such to PA for his/her perusal upon commencement of the PA’s employment. 10.2 The Primary Hiring Agent must read and understand the PA Training Guide and has properly explained to the PA his/her role and Page 1 of 6 AS03 (01/2026) responsibilities. 10.3 The PA is required to sign and acknowledge his/her receipt and understanding of the PA Training Guide prior to the issuance of the PA Card and Access Card by Manulife. 10.4 The PA is required to complete the Annual Compliance Refreshment Training for PA every year in accordance with the Company’s schedule. 10.5 PA who failed to fulfill the above compliance training requirements will be subject to de-registration. 11. The Hiring Agent(s) undertake all responsibilities in managing and supervising the PA in proper/confidential handling of personal data, including but not limited to that of Manulife’s clients (including potential and past clients), Manulife’s employees, Manulife’s agents and other PAs, prevention of Company and personal data information leakage, his/her proper conduct and behavior when the PA performs assigned duties upon the instructions of his/her Hiring Agent(s). 12. Manulife shall terminate the PA’s registration and access to Manulife’s systems without explanation and notice as a result of any misconduct, and/or non-compliance in the opinion of Manulife by the PA or violation of applicable laws and regulations by the PA or the PA takes part in any conduct, which in the opinion of Manulife, is detrimental or injurious or prejudicial to Manulife’s interests or reputation carried out during"});
